&lt;hr&gt;
&lt;h2 id="summary"&gt;Summary&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This problem is an entry-level GPU parallel computing question. Key points:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ol&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Index Calculation&lt;/strong&gt; - Master one-dimensional thread index mapping&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Boundary Check&lt;/strong&gt; - Prevent out-of-bounds access&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Coalesced Access&lt;/strong&gt; - Consecutive threads access consecutive memory&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Grid-Stride Loop&lt;/strong&gt; - Decouple grid configuration from data size&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Vectorization&lt;/strong&gt; - Reduce loop overhead&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;
&lt;p&gt;More complex optimization techniques will be introduced on this basis.&lt;/p&gt;</description></item></channel></rss>